        <bioghist id="ref58">
            <head>Historical/Biographical Note</head>
            <p>Americans for Progressive Israel (API) was founded in 1947 to function as a less ideologically-based support organization by the Hashomer Hatzair, a socialist-Zionist organization. API, now Meretz USA, publishes Israel Horizons (1952-present), is active in international Zionist work, and conducts educational programs. This unprocessed collection consists mainly of API's research files on topics of concern.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent id="ref1">
            <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
            <p>The collection focuses on events and issues in Israel, notably Israel's relations with the Arab world, and contains correspondnce, minutes, annual reports and other administrative matial. There is also some correspondence and administrative material, including minutes and 
                <emph render="italic">annual reports</emph>.</p>
        </scopecontent>
